<subSubSection id="C33A651A98035A01DADCFECCD0DCFDF8" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9F369198035A01DADCFECCD0DCFDF8" blockId="31.[189,1399,327,537]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
In their very recently published study of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D1298035A01D967FECCD692FE81" authority=", Foley et al. (2017)" authorityName="Foley" authorityYear="2017" box="[774,1159,327,353]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B954EA8398035A01D967FECCD1B6FE81" box="[774,931,327,353]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Hipposideros</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB14B6098035A01D9D0FECCD692FE81" author="Foley" box="[945,1159,327,353]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Foley" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" pagination="1 - 18" refId="ref261574" refString="Foley N. M., Goodman S. M., Whelan C. V., Puechmaille S. J. &amp; Teeling E. (2017). Towards navigating the Minotaur's labyrinth: cryptic diversity and taxonomic revision within the speciose genus Hipposideros (Hipposideridae). Acta Chiropterologica 19 (1): 1 - 18. https: // doi. org / 10.3161 / 15081109 ACC 2017.19.1.001" type="journal article" year="2017">
Foley 
<emphasis id="B954EA8398035A01D99BFEC3D639FE81" box="[1018,1068,327,353]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al</emphasis>
. (2017)
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
found that the Cyt- 
<emphasis id="B954EA8398035A01DF09FECCD762FE81" box="[1384,1399,327,353]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">b</emphasis>
sequences for 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D1298035A01DB04FEE0D602FE65" authority="E. Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire, 1813" authorityName="E. Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire" authorityYear="1813" box="[357,1047,363,390]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="commersoni">
<emphasis id="B954EA8398035A01DB04FEE0D08CFE65" box="[357,665,363,389]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Hipposideros commersoni</emphasis>
E. Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire, 1813
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D1298035A01DE42FEE7D351FE4A" authority="Goodman et al., 2016" authorityName="Goodman" authorityYear="2016" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cryptovalorona">
<emphasis id="B954EA8398035A01DE42FEE7D6EEFE65" box="[1059,1275,363,389]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">H. cryptovalorona</emphasis>
Goodman 
<emphasis id="B954EA8398035A01DADCFE1AD2E5FE4A" box="[189,240,400,426]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">et al</emphasis>
., 2016
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D1298035A01DB2EFE1AD07AFE4B" authority="(Wagner, 1845)" baseAuthorityName="Wagner" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[335,623,400,427]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gigas">
<emphasis id="B954EA8398035A01DB2EFE1AD3A6FE4A" box="[335,435,401,426]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">H. gigas</emphasis>
(Wagner, 1845)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D1298035A01D8C9FE1AD1DBFE4B" authority="(Peters, 1852)" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[680,974,400,427]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vittatus">
<emphasis id="B954EA8398035A01D8C9FE1AD137FE4A" box="[680,802,401,426]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">H. vittatus</emphasis>
(Peters, 1852)
</taxonomicName>
are quite different from those of the other representatives of this genus, and therefore, they resurrected the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D1298035A01DE5CFE3ED767FE2E" authority="Gray, 1866" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1866" box="[1085,1394,436,463]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Macronycteris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Chiroptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B954EA8398035A01DE5CFE3ED6F2FE2E" box="[1085,1255,437,462]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Macronycteris</emphasis>
Gray, 1866
</taxonomicName>
. This division is also supported by the deviant karyotype, which in 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D1298035A01D9DAFE52D64DFE13" box="[955,1112,473,499]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B954EA8398035A01D9DAFE52D64DFE13" box="[955,1112,473,499]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Hipposideros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
counts 32 chromosomes and 
<quantity id="4CD89B7498035A01DA8EFE75D33FFDF8" box="[239,298,510,537]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3208" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" unit="in" value="52.0">52 in</quantity>
species assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="4C204D1298035A01D879FE74D0D7FDF8" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1866" box="[536,706,511,536]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Macronycteris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Chiroptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B954EA8398035A01D879FE74D0D7FDF8" box="[536,706,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Macronycteris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
